<concept id="concept_2B0C42538AD54DC59C89E7F4D566FA40">
  <title>SiteCatalyst purchase: Mbox</title>
  <shortdesc>Once the plug-in is installed, the SiteCatalyst purchase event
	 will be available as an mbox called 
	 <i>SiteCatalyst: purchase</i>. 
  </shortdesc>
  <prolog>
    <metadata>
      <othermeta name="solution" content="Target" />
      <othermeta name="topic" content="Advanced" />
    </metadata>
  </prolog>
  <conbody>
    <p>
      <note>As of April 17, 2014, the information in this section has been
		  deprecated, and is replaced by the 
		  <xref href="http://marketing.adobe.com/resources/help/en_US/target/a4t/" format="http" scope="external">Adobe Analytics as the Reporting Source for
			 Adobe Target</xref> functionality. Adobe is continuing to support the former
		  integration methods, but it is recommended that you use the new functionality.
		</note>
    </p>
    <p>You can select the mbox from the 
		<uicontrol>select an mbox</uicontrol> dropdown. 
	 </p>
    <p>
      <b>Representing campaign conversion</b>
    </p>
    <p>When selected as the campaign conversion mbox, revenue will be recorded
		in Target reports. 
	 </p>
  </conbody>
